WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.034 --> 00:00:03.037
<i>Epic theme playing...</i>

2
00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:11.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

3
00:03:03.968 --> 00:03:05.241
<i>You're sure?</i>

4
00:03:09.475 --> 00:03:11.357
With his own eyes. Your Grace.

5
00:03:19.650 --> 00:03:21.385
Uh...

6
00:03:23.237 --> 00:03:25.472
Stay here.
Tell. tell no one.

7
00:03:26.532 --> 00:03:29.309
Help me dress.

8
00:03:43.883 --> 00:03:45.575
Who knows?

9
00:03:48.929 --> 00:03:50.706
My handmaiden. Talya.

10
00:03:51.515 --> 00:03:54.668
<i>Some of the servants.</i>

11
00:03:58.522 --> 00:04:00.632
<i>I saw him last night...</i>

12
00:04:01.525 --> 00:04:04.678
before he...

13
00:04:07.698 --> 00:04:10.017
He told me he wished
for Aegon to be king.

14
00:04:18.751 --> 00:04:20.485
It is the truth.

15
00:04:21.295 --> 00:04:23.296
Uttered with his own lips.

16
00:04:23.380 --> 00:04:27.075
His last words to me and I
was the only one to hear it.

17
00:04:28.302 --> 00:04:29.745
And now he's dead.

18
00:04:59.917 --> 00:05:02.878
What is it that could
not have waited an hour?

19
00:05:02.962 --> 00:05:04.696
Was Dorne invaded?

20
00:05:08.133 --> 00:05:09.993
The King is dead.

21
00:05:19.937 --> 00:05:22.506
We grieve
for Viserys the Peaceful...

22
00:05:23.732 --> 00:05:25.383
our sovereign...

23
00:05:27.569 --> 00:05:28.762
our friend.

24
00:05:32.700 --> 00:05:34.434
But he has left us a gift.

25
00:05:37.955 --> 00:05:42.042
With his last breath. he impressed
upon the Queen his final wish:

26
00:05:42.126 --> 00:05:45.587
That his son. Aegon...

27
00:05:45.671 --> 00:05:49.825
should succeed him
as Lord of the Seven Kingdoms.

28
00:05:58.851 --> 00:06:01.102
Then we may proceed now
with the full assurance

29
00:06:01.186 --> 00:06:04.022
of his blessing
on our long-laid plans.

30
00:06:04.106 --> 00:06:06.024
Yes.
There is much to be done.

31
00:06:06.108 --> 00:06:07.651
as we've previously discussed.

32
00:06:07.735 --> 00:06:09.778
Now. there are two
among the captains

33
00:06:09.862 --> 00:06:12.489
of the City Watch that
remain loyal to Daemon.

34
00:06:12.573 --> 00:06:15.013
Let us replace them.
Lord Lannister.

35
00:06:15.097 --> 00:06:16.701
The Treasury is well in hand.

36
00:06:16.785 --> 00:06:18.747
The gold will be divided
for safekeeping.

37
00:06:18.831 --> 00:06:19.963
Let ravens
be sent to our allies.

38
00:06:20.047 --> 00:06:22.248
River run and High garden.

39
00:06:22.332 --> 00:06:23.750
Am I to understand that
members of the small council

40
00:06:23.834 --> 00:06:27.545
have been planning secretly
to install my son without me?

41
00:06:27.629 --> 00:06:31.174
My Queen. there was no need to
sully you with darkling schemes.

42
00:06:31.258 --> 00:06:33.009
I will not have this.

43
00:06:33.093 --> 00:06:35.136
To hear that you are plotting

44
00:06:35.220 --> 00:06:38.306
to replace the King's
chosen heir

45
00:06:38.390 --> 00:06:39.474
- with an imposter!
- His firstborn son

46
00:06:39.558 --> 00:06:42.602
- is hardly an imposter.
- Hundreds of lords

47
00:06:42.686 --> 00:06:45.355
and landed knights
swore fealty to the Princess.

48
00:06:45.439 --> 00:06:47.273
That was some 20
years ago. Most of them now dead.

49
00:06:47.357 --> 00:06:48.692
You heard the Lord Hand.

50
00:06:48.776 --> 00:06:51.178
Plot or no.
the King changed his mind.

51
00:06:51.862 --> 00:06:54.572
I am six-and-seventy years old.

52
00:06:54.656 --> 00:06:59.119
I have known Viserys longer
than any who sit at this table.

53
00:06:59.203 --> 00:07:00.662
And I will not believe
that he said this

54
00:07:00.746 --> 00:07:06.985
on his deathbed. alone. with only
the. the boy's mother as a witness.

55
00:07:07.878 --> 00:07:09.921
This is seizure!

56
00:07:10.005 --> 00:07:12.424
It is theft!
It is treason!

57
00:07:12.508 --> 00:07:16.302
- At the least. it is...
- Mind your tongue. Lyman.

58
00:07:16.386 --> 00:07:18.847
The King was
well last night...

59
00:07:18.931 --> 00:07:20.665
by all accounts.

60
00:07:21.850 --> 00:07:26.938
Which of you here can swear
that he died of his own accord?

61
00:07:27.022 --> 00:07:30.734
Which of us are you accusing
of regicide. Lord Beesbury?

62
00:07:30.818 --> 00:07:32.527
Whether it was one of you.

63
00:07:32.611 --> 00:07:35.155
or all of you. I care not.

64
00:07:35.239 --> 00:07:36.239
- I will have no part...
- Sit down!

65
00:07:36.323 --> 00:07:39.351
- Ahh!
- Ser Criston.

66
00:07:50.963 --> 00:07:54.491
Throw down your sword and
remove your cloak. Ser Criston.

67
00:07:56.343 --> 00:07:59.012
I am your Lord Commander.
Ser Criston.

68
00:07:59.096 --> 00:08:00.597
Cast down your sword.

69
00:08:00.681 --> 00:08:04.184
I will not suffer insults
to Her Grace the Queen.

70
00:08:04.268 --> 00:08:07.462
There was no insult to me. Ser
Criston. Y... Put aside your blade.

71
00:08:15.654 --> 00:08:18.556
- Has it come to this?
- Lord Commander. enough.

72
00:08:22.119 --> 00:08:26.706
- Let us have Lord Beesbury removed.
- No.

73
00:08:26.790 --> 00:08:30.151
The door remains shut
until we finish our business.

74
00:08:46.977 --> 00:08:48.603
Storm's End is of concern.

75
00:08:48.687 --> 00:08:52.065
We may not assume
the loyalty of Lord Borros.

76
00:08:52.149 --> 00:08:54.859
But he has four daughters.
all of them unmarried.

77
00:08:54.943 --> 00:08:58.029
- The right proposal...
- What of Rhaenyra?

78
00:08:58.113 --> 00:09:01.908
The former heir cannot. of
course. be allowed to remain free

79
00:09:01.992 --> 00:09:05.745
and draw support to her claim.

80
00:09:05.829 --> 00:09:08.289
- You mean to imprison her.
- She and her family

81
00:09:08.373 --> 00:09:09.624
will be given the opportunity

82
00:09:09.708 --> 00:09:13.086
to publicly swear obeisance
to the new King.

83
00:09:13.170 --> 00:09:15.088
She will never bend the knee.

84
00:09:15.172 --> 00:09:18.033
Nor will Daemon. which you know.

85
00:09:23.347 --> 00:09:25.040
You plan to kill them.

86
00:09:29.269 --> 00:09:31.646
And all here accede to this.

87
00:09:31.730 --> 00:09:34.065
Your father is correct. Your Grace.

88
00:09:34.149 --> 00:09:37.777
A living challenger invites
battle and bloodshed.

89
00:09:37.861 --> 00:09:39.779
It is unsavory. yes.

90
00:09:39.863 --> 00:09:43.283
But a sacrifice we must make
to secure Aegon's succession.

91
00:09:43.367 --> 00:09:46.286
And then there is
Daemon to consider.

92
00:09:46.370 --> 00:09:48.913
- The King wouldn't wish for any unsavory...
- But the King did not wish

93
00:09:48.997 --> 00:09:51.791
for the murder of his daughter!

94
00:09:51.875 --> 00:09:53.793
He loved her.
I will not have you deny this.

95
00:09:53.877 --> 00:09:55.837
- And yet...
- One more word. and I will have you removed

96
00:09:55.921 --> 00:09:57.989
from this chamber
and sent to the Wall!

97
00:10:08.559 --> 00:10:11.461
What do you suggest.
Your Grace?

98
00:10:13.981 --> 00:10:15.799
Time is of the essence.

99
00:10:26.660 --> 00:10:28.645
Lord Commander We sterling...

100
00:10:29.454 --> 00:10:31.998
take your knights
to Dragons tone.

101
00:10:32.082 --> 00:10:34.025
Be quick and be clean.

102
00:10:48.265 --> 00:10:49.893
I am Lord Commander
of the Kings guard.

103
00:10:53.645 --> 00:10:56.798
I recognize no authority
but the King's.

104
00:10:57.774 --> 00:10:59.717
And until there is one...

105
00:11:02.070 --> 00:11:04.013
I have no place here.

106
00:11:15.792 --> 00:11:16.709
<i>It is our fate. I think.</i>

107
00:11:16.793 --> 00:11:19.712
<i>to crave always what
is given to another.</i>

108
00:11:19.796 --> 00:11:24.092
If one possesses a thing.
the other will take it away.

109
00:11:24.176 --> 00:11:26.369
Yes. Princess.

110
00:11:29.181 --> 00:11:30.665
Where is Aegon?

111
00:11:33.852 --> 00:11:35.561
N-Not here.

112
00:11:35.645 --> 00:11:36.880
He's not in his rooms.

113
00:11:44.571 --> 00:11:45.930
Father.

114
00:11:55.207 --> 00:11:56.941
What's happened?

115
00:12:11.890 --> 00:12:15.143
- Your father...
- There is a beast beneath the boards.

116
00:12:15.227 --> 00:12:17.420
Oh. my dearest love.

117
00:12:38.583 --> 00:12:40.235
Ser Erryk.

118
00:12:43.797 --> 00:12:44.589
Where's the Prince?

119
00:12:44.673 --> 00:12:47.383
Forgive me. Lord Hand.
I do not know.

120
00:12:47.467 --> 00:12:50.803
But you're sworn
to protect him.

121
00:12:50.887 --> 00:12:52.638
He exploits his authority
to order me away.

122
00:12:52.722 --> 00:12:54.030
and then he evades me.
my Lord.

123
00:12:58.728 --> 00:13:01.509
I believe he may have
left the Keep secretly.

124
00:13:01.773 --> 00:13:03.441
gone into the city.

125
00:13:03.775 --> 00:13:05.969
Find him.

126
00:13:10.115 --> 00:13:12.658
Take no one else
but your brother.

127
00:13:12.742 --> 00:13:14.452
And remove
your white cloaks.

128
00:13:14.536 --> 00:13:16.404
None can know who you are
or what you seek...

129
00:13:17.289 --> 00:13:19.406
including the Queen.

130
00:13:19.490 --> 00:13:21.517
My Lord.

131
00:13:22.491 --> 00:13:25.280
Bring him to me. and me alone.
Ser Erryk.

132
00:13:43.773 --> 00:13:46.926
What is the meaning of this?

133
00:14:06.254 --> 00:14:08.114
Guard. Guard!

134
00:14:22.479 --> 00:14:25.440
Prince Aegon's not to be found
within the castle walls. Your Grace.

135
00:14:25.524 --> 00:14:27.872
Your father has sent Ser
Erryk into the city to find him.

136
00:14:30.445 --> 00:14:33.306
Ser Erryk knows Aegon.
He has the advantage.

137
00:14:40.288 --> 00:14:43.040
I trust again to you.
Ser Criston.

138
00:14:43.124 --> 00:14:44.917
and to your loyalty.

139
00:14:45.001 --> 00:14:48.588
Aegon must be found. and
he must be brought to me.

140
00:14:48.672 --> 00:14:50.740
The very fate of the Seven
Kingdoms depends on it.

141
00:14:51.925 --> 00:14:55.912
Everything you feel for me...
as your Queen.

142
00:14:57.347 --> 00:15:00.600
I will not fail you.

143
00:15:00.684 --> 00:15:01.684
I'll come with you.

144
00:15:01.768 --> 00:15:04.979
That would not be
my desire. Aemond.

145
00:15:05.063 --> 00:15:09.942
- If anything has happened...
- Cole needs me. Mother.

146
00:15:10.026 --> 00:15:13.388
Ser Erryk isn't the only one
who knows Aegon's doings.

147
00:15:39.598 --> 00:15:41.224
<i>Aegon brought
me to the Street of Silk</i>

148
00:15:41.308 --> 00:15:42.850
on my thirteenth name day.

149
00:15:42.934 --> 00:15:46.145
It was his duty
as my brother. he said.

150
00:15:46.229 --> 00:15:49.549
to ensure I was
as educated as he was.

151
00:15:53.445 --> 00:15:55.930
At least that's what
I understood him to mean.

152
00:15:59.242 --> 00:16:01.077
I don't follow.

153
00:16:01.161 --> 00:16:02.828
He said.
“Time to get it wet.”

154
00:16:02.912 --> 00:16:05.915
Every woman is
an image of the Mother.

155
00:16:05.999 --> 00:16:07.442
to be spoken of
with reverence.

156
00:16:16.384 --> 00:16:17.635
<i>Sometime last night. we...</i>

157
00:16:17.719 --> 00:16:21.138
<i>misplaced
our drinking companion.</i>

158
00:16:21.222 --> 00:16:24.684
<i>Knowing that he has been. in the
past. a patron of your fine establishment.</i>

159
00:16:24.768 --> 00:16:27.016
<i>we thought to inquire here
as to his whereabouts.</i>

160
00:16:27.181 --> 00:16:28.623
And describe him.

161
00:16:29.648 --> 00:16:31.883
That is a delicate matter.

162
00:16:32.710 --> 00:16:34.439
You see. the man we seek

163
00:16:34.523 --> 00:16:35.861
is the young Prince Aegon.

164
00:16:35.945 --> 00:16:39.557
I may trust. I hope.
in the discretion of your trade.

165
00:16:40.784 --> 00:16:42.868
The Prince is not here.

166
00:16:42.952 --> 00:16:47.665
Has he been here?
Earlier. perhaps?

167
00:16:47.749 --> 00:16:51.903
- Quite a bit earlier. Years ago. in fact.
- But more recently?

168
00:16:53.588 --> 00:16:56.799
He does not frequent
the Street of Silk.

169
00:16:56.883 --> 00:16:59.160
His tastes are known to be...

170
00:16:59.636 --> 00:17:02.455
less discriminating.

171
00:17:03.139 --> 00:17:04.290
Meaning what?

172
00:17:05.767 --> 00:17:10.880
I wish you luck. good Ser.
And my best to your friend.

173
00:17:16.528 --> 00:17:19.013
How you've grown.

174
00:17:21.992 --> 00:17:25.144
Hm.

175
00:17:26.621 --> 00:17:28.748
Viserys amended his wishes.

176
00:17:28.832 --> 00:17:30.900
It's as simple as that.

177
00:17:32.127 --> 00:17:35.046
You once swore
your banners to Rhaenyra.

178
00:17:35.130 --> 00:17:37.089
You must now

179
00:17:37.173 --> 00:17:39.951
pledge them
to the future king.

180
00:17:46.683 --> 00:17:51.937
I must confer first
with my house on this matter.

181
00:17:52.021 --> 00:17:55.174
You'll not leave this room
without declaring your intention.

182
00:18:04.701 --> 00:18:07.937
I am no oath breaker.

183
00:18:10.540 --> 00:18:12.483
I will not bend the knee.

184
00:18:19.632 --> 00:18:22.118
Anyone else?

185
00:18:34.063 --> 00:18:38.176
House Fell... keeps its
sworn oath to the Princess.

186
00:18:41.488 --> 00:18:43.681
Very well.

187
00:19:03.593 --> 00:19:04.802
Long live the King.

188
00:19:04.886 --> 00:19:07.830
Long live the King.

189
00:19:38.795 --> 00:19:41.672
<i>It seems you were
mistaken as to Aegon's habits.</i>

190
00:19:41.756 --> 00:19:44.383
<i>He could be in
the hands of mercenaries.</i>

191
00:19:44.467 --> 00:19:46.035
<i>on a ship to Yi Ti.</i>

192
00:19:46.886 --> 00:19:49.013
<i>He could be dead.</i>

193
00:19:49.097 --> 00:19:51.486
Let us hope. for your mother's
sake. that is not the case.

194
00:20:07.323 --> 00:20:08.866
Let's have a look.

195
00:20:08.950 --> 00:20:11.452
- Go on.
- Come here. Come here!

196
00:20:11.536 --> 00:20:14.438
Get in there. you little...

197
00:20:20.545 --> 00:20:21.862
Yeah!

198
00:20:23.047 --> 00:20:26.158
Come on!

199
00:20:31.014 --> 00:20:34.100
- Arryk
- How old are they?

200
00:20:34.184 --> 00:20:37.728
About 10 years. I should say.

201
00:20:37.812 --> 00:20:40.981
They have them grow
their nails and file the teeth.

202
00:20:41.065 --> 00:20:42.508
Makes them more formidable.

203
00:20:43.864 --> 00:20:47.655
- Come on!
- Prince Aegon spends many a night in this place.

204
00:20:47.739 --> 00:20:49.990
Do you see now what he is?

205
00:20:50.074 --> 00:20:51.475
<i>You've not seen everything.</i>

206
00:21:00.001 --> 00:21:03.029
Aegon's?
One of many. I'd wager.

207
00:21:19.562 --> 00:21:22.690
Here I am. trawling
the city. ever the good soldier

208
00:21:22.774 --> 00:21:26.385
in search of a wastrel who's never
taken half an interest in his birthright.

209
00:21:29.113 --> 00:21:31.949
'Tis I the younger brother who
studies history and philosophy.

210
00:21:32.033 --> 00:21:33.659
it is I who trains
with the sword.

211
00:21:33.743 --> 00:21:34.702
who rides the largest
dragon in the world.

212
00:21:34.786 --> 00:21:37.271
It is I who should be...

213
00:21:40.667 --> 00:21:43.627
I know what it is to toil for
what others are freely given.

214
00:21:43.711 --> 00:21:45.571
Mm.

215
00:21:47.966 --> 00:21:50.593
And we can't find him. Cole.

216
00:21:50.677 --> 00:21:53.679
You are a decent man
with no taste for depravity.

217
00:21:53.763 --> 00:21:55.681
His secrets are his own...

218
00:21:55.765 --> 00:21:57.057
and he's welcome to them.

219
00:21:57.141 --> 00:21:59.852
I'm next in line
to the throne.

220
00:21:59.936 --> 00:22:02.438
Should they come
looking for me.

221
00:22:02.522 --> 00:22:04.298
I intend to be found.

222
00:22:14.117 --> 00:22:17.161
<i>Something must
be done. Aegon is unfit to rule.</i>

223
00:22:17.245 --> 00:22:19.079
You tolerated the Prince's
proclivities for years.

224
00:22:19.163 --> 00:22:20.080
Because it was
my sworn duty. Arryk.

225
00:22:20.164 --> 00:22:22.041
It's for the Hand
to find wisdom.

226
00:22:22.125 --> 00:22:25.210
We swore an oath
of service until death.

227
00:22:25.294 --> 00:22:28.213
A moment of your time. m'lords.

228
00:22:28.297 --> 00:22:30.366
You'll find no buyers
for your wares here.

229
00:22:34.762 --> 00:22:37.915
I can take you to Prince Aegon.

230
00:22:38.141 --> 00:22:41.143
Rather. I am sent by one
who knows where he is.

231
00:22:41.227 --> 00:22:42.495
Who'll tell you. for a price.

232
00:22:44.856 --> 00:22:47.483
Deliver him. and we'll
consider your price.

233
00:22:47.567 --> 00:22:52.446
My mistress will not treat
with the servants of the Keep...

234
00:22:52.530 --> 00:22:55.282
exalted though they may be.

235
00:22:55.366 --> 00:22:57.701
She'll trust this to
the Hand of the King only.

236
00:22:57.785 --> 00:22:59.787
Impossible.

237
00:22:59.871 --> 00:23:03.899
I think he will wish to hear what
the White Worm can tell him.

238
00:23:20.016 --> 00:23:21.876
Halt! Hold the gate!

239
00:23:24.854 --> 00:23:26.105
Let go of me!

240
00:23:26.189 --> 00:23:27.898
<i>He was fleeing from the gate.</i>

241
00:23:27.982 --> 00:23:28.774
Do you know who I am?

242
00:23:28.858 --> 00:23:30.484
<i>A warning for the Princess.</i>

243
00:23:30.568 --> 00:23:33.445
<i>I'd wager.</i>

244
00:23:33.529 --> 00:23:34.763
What say you?

245
00:23:36.032 --> 00:23:39.018
The Lord Confessor
presumes.

246
00:23:40.411 --> 00:23:42.913
I have no love
for the Princess.

247
00:23:42.997 --> 00:23:46.317
And where were you going then
with such urgency?

248
00:23:52.048 --> 00:23:54.283
Let the King's Justice take him.

249
00:23:58.513 --> 00:23:59.513
Let go of me!

250
00:23:59.597 --> 00:24:02.349
- No! This is not right!
- You did well. Lord Larys.

251
00:24:02.433 --> 00:24:05.872
- I will...
- Only my duty. my Lord Hand.

252
00:24:05.956 --> 00:24:07.177
Who do you think you are?

253
00:24:07.261 --> 00:24:09.579
You've spent many hours
with the Queen of late.

254
00:24:15.738 --> 00:24:21.143
There's no reason those hours
could not. in the end. benefit you.

255
00:25:50.708 --> 00:25:53.877
I will do you the considerable
courtesy of assuming

256
00:25:53.961 --> 00:25:55.879
there is a good reason
for the outrage

257
00:25:55.963 --> 00:25:57.990
of my treatment
here this morning.

258
00:25:59.008 --> 00:26:01.577
My sincerest regrets
for the lack of ceremony.

259
00:26:04.889 --> 00:26:06.332
The King.

260
00:26:11.354 --> 00:26:14.106
And you are
usurping the throne.

261
00:26:14.190 --> 00:26:16.108
It was my husband's
dying wish.

262
00:26:16.192 --> 00:26:17.109
Believe it or no.

263
00:26:17.193 --> 00:26:19.903
it is of no consequence.

264
00:26:19.987 --> 00:26:21.388
Aegon will be king.

265
00:26:24.867 --> 00:26:27.452
I came here
to ask your support.

266
00:26:27.536 --> 00:26:31.081
Well. I must credit you
for your boldness.

267
00:26:31.165 --> 00:26:33.167
House Velaryon
has long allied itself

268
00:26:33.251 --> 00:26:35.652
with the Princess Rhaenyra
and what has it gained you?

269
00:26:37.630 --> 00:26:40.949
Your daughter dead...
alone in Pentos.

270
00:26:41.926 --> 00:26:43.719
Your son cuckolded.

271
00:26:43.803 --> 00:26:46.163
Rhaenyra's heirs
are none of yours.

272
00:26:47.348 --> 00:26:52.311
It is your husband who grasps
so heedlessly for the throne.

273
00:26:52.395 --> 00:26:54.188
And even he
has abandoned you:

274
00:26:54.272 --> 00:26:56.899
Gone these six long years
to fight a desperate battle.

275
00:26:56.983 --> 00:27:00.068
returning grievously.
if not mortally. wounded.

276
00:27:00.152 --> 00:27:02.888
leaving the Lady of Driftmark
to chart her course alone.

277
00:27:05.574 --> 00:27:08.602
The word of my house
is not fickle.

278
00:27:10.621 --> 00:27:13.816
No. But. dear cousin...

279
00:27:15.543 --> 00:27:19.671
you more than any soul alive
understand what I say now.

280
00:27:19.755 --> 00:27:21.381
Princess Rhaenys.
I loved my husband.

281
00:27:21.465 --> 00:27:24.410
but I will speak
the truth we both know.

282
00:27:25.011 --> 00:27:26.870
You should've been queen.

283
00:27:29.348 --> 00:27:31.516
I little thought to hear
those words from you.

284
00:27:31.600 --> 00:27:34.344
The Iron Throne was yours
by blood and by temperament.

285
00:27:34.428 --> 00:27:37.147
Viserys would've lived
his days a country lord.

286
00:27:37.231 --> 00:27:39.149
content to hunt
and study his histories.

287
00:27:39.233 --> 00:27:40.676
but... here we are.

288
00:27:43.555 --> 00:27:44.571
We do not rule

289
00:27:44.655 --> 00:27:48.075
but we may guide
the men that do.

290
00:27:48.159 --> 00:27:49.868
Gently...

291
00:27:49.952 --> 00:27:52.246
away from violence
and sure destruction

292
00:27:52.330 --> 00:27:55.123
- and instead toward peace.
- Ugh.

293
00:27:55.207 --> 00:27:58.377
Is it in the name of peace
that you've imprisoned me?

294
00:27:58.461 --> 00:28:00.629
- And what of my dragon?
- If we are over matched.

295
00:28:00.713 --> 00:28:03.157
Rhaenyra will be tempted to
strike us. and war will ensue.

296
00:28:04.967 --> 00:28:08.328
Without your dragon. she
may be persuaded to negotiate.

297
00:28:09.722 --> 00:28:12.683
If it's Driftmark you want.
you shall have it

298
00:28:12.767 --> 00:28:17.296
for you and your granddaughters
to pass on as you see fit.

299
00:28:21.942 --> 00:28:23.760
You are wiser than
I believed you to be...

300
00:28:27.948 --> 00:28:30.242
Alicent High tower.

301
00:28:30.326 --> 00:28:33.937
A true queen counts
the cost to her people.

302
00:28:35.039 --> 00:28:38.625
And yet you toil still
in service to men.

303
00:28:38.709 --> 00:28:41.737
Your father.
your husband. your son.

304
00:28:43.506 --> 00:28:45.132
You desire not to be free.

305
00:28:45.216 --> 00:28:48.410
but to make a window
in the wall of your prison.

306
00:28:49.220 --> 00:28:52.848
Have you never
imagined yourself...

307
00:28:52.932 --> 00:28:56.084
on the Iron Throne?

308
00:29:07.196 --> 00:29:09.181
I'll leave you
with your thoughts.

309
00:29:11.867 --> 00:29:13.894
Ring the bell when
you have an answer.

310
00:29:38.269 --> 00:29:39.670
My Prince.

311
00:29:48.779 --> 00:29:52.891
You yourself are the mysterious
White Worm. I take it.

312
00:29:55.161 --> 00:29:59.147
Or are you simply a further
peel in this stinking onion?

313
00:30:00.958 --> 00:30:04.027
My condolences
on the passing of your king.

314
00:30:19.018 --> 00:30:20.352
Where is Prince Aegon?

315
00:30:20.436 --> 00:30:27.109
I thought. the Prince is in Flea
Bottom where no one is to be trusted.

316
00:30:27.193 --> 00:30:29.486
I'd best secrete him
somewhere safe

317
00:30:29.570 --> 00:30:32.322
in case they come
looking for him.

318
00:30:32.406 --> 00:30:34.533
Where's the Prince?

319
00:30:34.617 --> 00:30:37.311
He is safely tucked away.

320
00:30:38.621 --> 00:30:42.165
I want an end
to the savage use

321
00:30:42.249 --> 00:30:44.292
of children in Flea Bottom.

322
00:30:44.376 --> 00:30:47.629
They are forced to fight.
and worse...

323
00:30:47.713 --> 00:30:50.866
your gold cloaks take the
bribes given them to look away.

324
00:30:52.468 --> 00:30:54.803
An obscenity

325
00:30:54.887 --> 00:30:58.999
either tolerated
or ignored by the crown.

326
00:31:00.643 --> 00:31:02.602
I'll look into it.

327
00:31:02.686 --> 00:31:04.421
You have my word.

328
00:31:09.568 --> 00:31:11.319
When your plots ripen

329
00:31:11.403 --> 00:31:14.656
and you install your grandson
on the throne.

330
00:31:14.740 --> 00:31:17.909
remember it was me
who put him there.

331
00:31:17.993 --> 00:31:22.956
I could have killed him
as easily as a wasp on fruit.

332
00:31:23.040 --> 00:31:28.153
There is no power but what
the people allow you to take.

333
00:31:30.714 --> 00:31:31.907
I will remember.

334
00:31:55.864 --> 00:31:58.600
Listen.

335
00:32:06.792 --> 00:32:08.819
No... No!

336
00:32:09.545 --> 00:32:11.697
No! Agh!

337
00:32:19.221 --> 00:32:21.431
Where is the White Worm?

338
00:32:21.515 --> 00:32:22.682
She sold you for a price.

339
00:32:22.766 --> 00:32:24.000
And why have you paid it?

340
00:32:26.186 --> 00:32:28.730
I want my mother.

341
00:32:28.814 --> 00:32:30.524
Your grandfather. the Hand.

342
00:32:30.608 --> 00:32:32.634
will meet you
outside the city walls.

343
00:32:40.743 --> 00:32:42.269
You flee what other men
die seeking. Aegon.

344
00:32:59.803 --> 00:33:01.037
I do regret this. friend.

345
00:33:31.877 --> 00:33:34.654
No! Stop! No.

346
00:33:38.634 --> 00:33:41.886
- I was hoping you disappeared.
- Is our father truly dead?

347
00:33:41.970 --> 00:33:44.264
Yes... and they're
going to make you king.

348
00:33:44.348 --> 00:33:47.058
Agh!

349
00:33:47.142 --> 00:33:49.336
- No!
- Are you going to help me?!

350
00:33:51.980 --> 00:33:54.441
No! Let me go!

351
00:33:54.525 --> 00:33:55.675
Where's your brother. huh?

352
00:33:57.528 --> 00:33:59.237
Let me go!

353
00:33:59.321 --> 00:34:01.807
Brother! Ahh!

354
00:34:07.705 --> 00:34:09.397
Let me go!

355
00:34:09.957 --> 00:34:11.916
I have no wish to rule!

356
00:34:12.000 --> 00:34:14.628
No taste for duty!
I'm not suited.

357
00:34:14.712 --> 00:34:16.212
You'll get no argument from me.

358
00:34:16.296 --> 00:34:20.008
You let me go. I will
find a ship and sail away.

359
00:34:20.092 --> 00:34:21.284
never to be found.

360
00:34:25.180 --> 00:34:26.915
The Queen awaits.

361
00:34:57.629 --> 00:35:00.757
- Well played.
- None of this is a game.

362
00:35:00.841 --> 00:35:03.076
And yet you treat it as one.

363
00:35:04.303 --> 00:35:05.011
A charming contest.

364
00:35:05.095 --> 00:35:10.000
the... prize.
a pouch of silver.

365
00:35:14.521 --> 00:35:16.690
We have relied on one
another these many years.

366
00:35:16.774 --> 00:35:21.569
And now it is the good of
the family that we both desire.

367
00:35:21.653 --> 00:35:25.015
Whatever our differences.
our hearts remain as one.

368
00:35:26.909 --> 00:35:28.785
Our hearts were never one.

369
00:35:28.869 --> 00:35:30.495
I see that now.

370
00:35:30.579 --> 00:35:32.372
Rather. I have been a piece
that you moved about the board.

371
00:35:32.456 --> 00:35:38.795
If that is true. then I made you
Queen of the Seven Kingdoms.

372
00:35:38.879 --> 00:35:43.007
- Would you have desired it otherwise?
- How could I know?

373
00:35:43.091 --> 00:35:46.202
I wanted whatever you
impressed upon me to want.

374
00:35:47.638 --> 00:35:50.140
And now the debt comes due.

375
00:35:50.224 --> 00:35:53.184
- A debt you were happy enough to pay.
- A sacrifice.

376
00:35:53.268 --> 00:35:58.023
A sacrifice made for
the stability of the realm.

377
00:35:58.107 --> 00:36:00.191
No king has ever lived
that hasn't had to forfeit

378
00:36:00.275 --> 00:36:02.360
the lives of a few
to protect the many.

379
00:36:02.444 --> 00:36:04.654
Though I understand
your squeamishness.

380
00:36:04.738 --> 00:36:08.350
Reluctance to murder
is not a weakness!

381
00:36:11.995 --> 00:36:12.787
I have Aegon.

382
00:36:12.871 --> 00:36:15.607
We'll proceed now as I see fit.

383
00:36:22.297 --> 00:36:25.425
We will send terms
to Rhaenyra on Dragons tone.

384
00:36:25.509 --> 00:36:28.553
True terms. such that she
may accept without shame.

385
00:36:28.637 --> 00:36:32.390
If she lives. her allies will
mass behind her banners.

386
00:36:32.474 --> 00:36:35.210
- looking for her return.
- Then she must not return.

387
00:36:36.478 --> 00:36:38.062
My husband would have
desired this mercy be shown

388
00:36:38.146 --> 00:36:40.899
- to his daughter.
- Your husband?

389
00:36:40.983 --> 00:36:43.843
Or you. his daughter's
childhood companion?

390
00:36:48.323 --> 00:36:51.476
Criston Cole will be named Lord
Commander of the Kings guard.

391
00:36:52.953 --> 00:36:55.497
My son will be anointed
tomorrow at dawn.

392
00:36:55.581 --> 00:36:59.083
The whole of King's Landing
must witness his ascent.

393
00:36:59.167 --> 00:37:02.796
He will assume authority.
There will be no more dithering.

394
00:37:02.880 --> 00:37:05.298
My son will take the crown of
his namesake. the Conqueror.

395
00:37:05.382 --> 00:37:07.467
and carry Blackfyre.
his sword.

396
00:37:07.551 --> 00:37:11.121
Let the people remember the
ancient strength of House Targaryen.

397
00:37:15.100 --> 00:37:18.211
You look so much like
your mother in certain lights.

398
00:37:27.112 --> 00:37:30.640
As you wish.

399
00:37:42.502 --> 00:37:44.446
Your Grace.

400
00:37:46.965 --> 00:37:51.344
The hour is late. Lord Larys.

401
00:37:51.428 --> 00:37:54.456
I've found out something
that you should know.

402
00:38:06.068 --> 00:38:10.238
Have you asked yourself.
I wonder...

403
00:38:10.322 --> 00:38:12.615
how it is...

404
00:38:12.699 --> 00:38:14.476
That your father. the Hand...

405
00:38:15.744 --> 00:38:18.897
found Aegon first?

406
00:38:51.655 --> 00:38:55.366
There is a web of spies
at work in the Red Keep.

407
00:38:55.450 --> 00:39:00.330
Along its threads travels news
of all our doings.

408
00:39:00.414 --> 00:39:05.877
Your father knows this.
but has left it in place.

409
00:39:05.961 --> 00:39:09.531
More than once. it has proved
advantageous to those willing to...

410
00:39:11.008 --> 00:39:13.409
feed the weaver.

411
00:39:14.803 --> 00:39:16.788
And this weaver watches me?

412
00:39:18.682 --> 00:39:20.834
Um...

413
00:39:40.579 --> 00:39:46.192
One of the little spiders
is your lady-in-waiting.

414
00:39:48.003 --> 00:39:50.880
- Talya?
- There are more like her.

415
00:39:50.964 --> 00:39:53.199
Even I do not know their number.

416
00:39:57.637 --> 00:40:01.933
There is one way
to destroy his advantage.

417
00:40:02.017 --> 00:40:05.086
It must be taken out
at the head.

418
00:40:06.688 --> 00:40:11.759
When the Queen dies.
the bees fly without purpose.

419
00:40:13.361 --> 00:40:16.472
Begging your pardon for the
turn of phrase. Your Grace.

420
00:40:17.407 --> 00:40:21.661
I assume this task falls
within your expertise.

421
00:40:21.745 --> 00:40:24.898
If you wish it...

422
00:40:25.082 --> 00:40:26.691
it will be done.

423
00:41:45.495 --> 00:41:48.314
Out of my way!

424
00:41:55.505 --> 00:41:56.255
With me. Princess.

425
00:41:56.339 --> 00:41:58.992
I cannot let this
treachery stand.

426
00:42:38.381 --> 00:42:41.659
- Where are we?
- Just south of King's Way.

427
00:42:43.428 --> 00:42:44.662
The Blackwater's this way.

428
00:43:13.625 --> 00:43:16.210
I won't leave Meleys.

429
00:43:16.294 --> 00:43:17.378
- If I could get to the Dragon pit. then...
- No.

430
00:43:17.462 --> 00:43:19.172
They'll expect you there.
Princess.

431
00:43:19.256 --> 00:43:22.241
You won't get
past the gates.

432
00:43:22.550 --> 00:43:24.302
Now come.

433
00:43:24.386 --> 00:43:26.512
You must make for the
riverfront and find a ship.

434
00:43:26.596 --> 00:43:28.347
Before they know you've gone.

435
00:43:28.431 --> 00:43:30.516
Move it! Go! Go!

436
00:43:30.600 --> 00:43:32.059
This way!

437
00:43:32.143 --> 00:43:34.812
Keep moving! That's right.

438
00:43:34.896 --> 00:43:36.297
That's right!

439
00:43:38.066 --> 00:43:39.233
- Onward!
- This way.

440
00:43:39.317 --> 00:43:42.303
Halt! Halt!

441
00:43:44.739 --> 00:43:46.766
Keep moving!

442
00:43:51.454 --> 00:43:54.232
All of you. move forward!

443
00:43:56.710 --> 00:43:59.112
Keep moving!

444
00:44:11.224 --> 00:44:13.809
Out of the way!

445
00:44:13.893 --> 00:44:15.962
Out of the way!

446
00:44:30.577 --> 00:44:32.270
Hyah! Hyah!

447
00:44:36.082 --> 00:44:38.709
Have the
decency to look grateful.

448
00:44:38.793 --> 00:44:42.447
Do you know what has been
done to give you this day?

449
00:44:45.550 --> 00:44:47.468
In an hour. you will be king.

450
00:44:47.552 --> 00:44:50.388
- And my father never wanted this.
- That's not true.

451
00:44:50.472 --> 00:44:52.556
He had 20 years to name me heir
and never did.

452
00:44:52.640 --> 00:44:55.476
Steadfastly. he upheld
Rhaenyra's claim.

453
00:44:55.560 --> 00:44:58.754
- He changed his mind.
- Oh.

454
00:45:00.648 --> 00:45:01.274
No...

455
00:45:01.358 --> 00:45:05.278
He could have.
but he never did

456
00:45:05.362 --> 00:45:06.888
because he didn't like me.

457
00:45:08.281 --> 00:45:10.533
And yet. with his final breath.

458
00:45:10.617 --> 00:45:13.245
he whispered to me that you
should take his place on the throne.

459
00:45:34.015 --> 00:45:37.418
- Do not toy with me. Mother.
- I speak the truth.

460
00:45:51.950 --> 00:45:54.243
Listen to me. Aegon.

461
00:45:54.327 --> 00:45:55.619
Your grandfather. the Hand.
will try to impress on you

462
00:45:55.703 --> 00:45:58.414
that Rhaenyra should be
put to the sword.

463
00:45:58.498 --> 00:46:01.625
You must reject this counsel.

464
00:46:01.709 --> 00:46:03.586
We must not rule with
cruelty and callousness.

465
00:46:03.670 --> 00:46:05.504
For all her faults.
she is your sister.

466
00:46:05.588 --> 00:46:08.199
- your. your father's daughter...
- Do you love me?

467
00:46:10.760 --> 00:46:13.346
You imbecile.

468
00:46:13.430 --> 00:46:16.123
Make way for the royal wheelhouse!

469
00:46:32.115 --> 00:46:34.225
Hey. hey. forward then.

470
00:46:35.785 --> 00:46:38.354
Go on. move yourself! Come on!

471
00:47:39.849 --> 00:47:42.393
People of King's Landing...

472
00:47:42.477 --> 00:47:45.338
today is the saddest of days.

473
00:47:45.855 --> 00:47:49.066
Our beloved king...

474
00:47:49.150 --> 00:47:51.844
Viserys the Peaceful...

475
00:47:52.195 --> 00:47:54.639
is dead.

476
00:47:59.911 --> 00:48:04.482
But it is also the most
joyous of days...

477
00:48:05.458 --> 00:48:08.235
for as his spirit left us...

478
00:48:10.255 --> 00:48:11.630
he whispered his final wish:

479
00:48:11.714 --> 00:48:16.952
That his firstborn son. Aegon...

480
00:48:18.179 --> 00:48:20.581
should succeed him.

481
00:48:30.358 --> 00:48:32.802
Guards!

482
00:48:34.112 --> 00:48:36.555
Out of the way! Move!

483
00:48:44.956 --> 00:48:46.165
Halt!

484
00:48:46.249 --> 00:48:47.692
Turn!

485
00:48:56.759 --> 00:48:58.802
Present...

486
00:48:58.886 --> 00:49:02.039
arms!

487
00:49:33.463 --> 00:49:36.549
It is your great
good fortune and privilege

488
00:49:36.633 --> 00:49:39.160
to be here to witness this:

489
00:49:41.012 --> 00:49:43.622
A new day for our city...

490
00:49:44.474 --> 00:49:46.517
a new day for our realm.

491
00:49:46.601 --> 00:49:51.881
A new king... to lead us.

492
00:50:49.247 --> 00:50:53.108
May the
Warrior give him courage.

493
00:50:55.920 --> 00:51:00.533
May the Smith lend strength
to his sword and shield.

494
00:51:02.677 --> 00:51:05.704
May the Father
defend him in his need.

495
00:51:08.057 --> 00:51:12.811
May the Crone
lift her shining lamp

496
00:51:12.895 --> 00:51:16.298
and light his way to wisdom.

497
00:51:40.465 --> 00:51:41.965
The crown of the Conqueror.

498
00:51:42.049 --> 00:51:44.201
passed down
through generations.

499
00:52:02.195 --> 00:52:04.613
Let the Seven bear witness:

500
00:52:04.697 --> 00:52:07.600
Aegon Targaryen is the
true heir to the Iron Throne.

501
00:52:43.402 --> 00:52:48.115
All hail His Grace.
Aegon.

502
00:52:48.199 --> 00:52:50.033
Second of his Name.

503
00:52:50.117 --> 00:52:53.704
King of the Andals and the
Rhoynar and the First Men.

504
00:52:53.788 --> 00:52:56.123
Lord of the Seven Kingdoms

